HashMap
A HashMap in Java is a data structure that stores data in key → value pairs.
HashMap<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

ye internally map (interface ) ko extence kiye hue hai

Method :

void clear()
V compute(K key, BiFunction<? super K,? super V,? extends V> remappingFunction)
=key ke liye value nikaal — agar hai toh use use kar, nahi hai toh null se start kar.
=  map.put("A", 10);
=  map.compute("A", (k, v) -> v + 5);  // A=15

V computeIfAbsent(K key, Function<? super K,? extends V> mappingFunction)
= Agar key absent hai, tabhi value bana aur daal. Warna kuch mat kar.
= map.computeIfAbsent("A", k -> 10); // A=10;

V computeIfPresent(K key, BiFunction<? super K,? super V,? extends V> remappingFunction)
= Agar key present hai, tabhi update kar. Warna ignore
=  map.computeIfPresent("B", (k, v) -> v + 5);

